The gig economy is changing the way people and businesses think about work. Many companies are now outsourcing projects to freelancers as they seek more convenience in finding an expert without going through a lengthy hiring process.

However, hiring a freelancer is not a decision to take lightly. Here are some pros and cons of hiring a freelance specialist for businesses to consider.

Pros
ğŸ”¹ Less cost
Hiring a freelancer means you only pay them for the work they do. This is one of the efficient ways you can control your cost.

ğŸ”¹ Access to highly talent
There are many freelance marketplaces for you to find extraordinary talent with the exact skills you need, which can be a worthy investment for your business.

ğŸ”¹ Get more work done
Freelancers have complete control of their hours. So, they can spend more hours on your projects as they don't typically depend on the usual business hour.

Cons
ğŸ”¸ Risk in hiring a freelancer
You might need to conduct a thorough interview and require their portfolio to verify that they possess the skills you need before you hit the ground running.

ğŸ”¸ They could disappear
Some freelancers could be challenging communicating with, even during hiring. Or they might disappear after you give them an assignment and never come back again.

ğŸ”¸ Challenge to meet your specific guideline
Unlike an in-house employee, it can be challenging for an employer to get freelancers to follow a specific guideline. So, you can expect different working styles from freelancers as they come from diverse backgrounds.

Hiring the right freelancer can be incredibly beneficial for your business. Make your investment in hiring freelancers worth it by ensuring you are thorough when looking for a freelance specialist and offer fair compensation to your freelancer if you want to keep them with you in the long run.

Laptop battery is one of the deviceâ€™s most essential parts that require well maintenance. ğŸ”‹ğŸ’»  There are advice and rules suggested on- and off-internet on how to maintain your battery lifespan.

While there are certain truths, there are also misconceptions that we should completely ignore. Letâ€™s debunk some of the common battery myths! ğŸ‘‡

ğŸš© Myth 1: Charge the laptop battery to full power right out of the box before using.
ğŸ” Truth:  This might apply to devices with nickel-based batteries of the early 2000s. But most of the devices nowadays run on lithium-ion (LI) batteries, which are ready to work as soon as you turn them on. 

ğŸš© Myth 2: Wait for your laptop battery to run low before you charge it again, or you will shorten the battery lifespan.
ğŸ” Truth: The extreme discharges might cause your laptop to show wrong battery life estimates instead. And Lithium-ion (LI) batteries last longer if you never let them drain completely.

ğŸš© Myth 3: You can easily replace laptop batteries by yourself.
ğŸ” Truth: Replacing a built-in battery requires advanced techniques. Unless you are a well-versed user or a technician, consider relying on an IT professional to get the replacement done for you.

Keepers of the Horizon

The kidswear story centres on British country dress. Soft tweed jackets with patch pockets sit over kilted skirts or tartan shorts; corduroy coats are cut with rounded collars; duffles are trimmed with toggles and sleeve turn-backs. Shirts carry oxford stripes or micro florals. Knitwear includes oatmeal fair isles, mossy cables, and patterned yokes, sometimes layered over collared shirting and worn with chinos or cords. Bucket hats, ribbed beanies and wellington boots complete the portfolio.

AMDâ€™s @jack_huynh SVP and GM, Computing and Graphics Group, and Mark Cerny, lead architect of PS5 and PS5 Pro, discuss the latest developments from Project Amethyst â€“ the collaboration between Sony Interactive Entertainment and AMD focused on Machine Learning-based technology for graphics and gameplay â€“ a shared commitment to push gaming technology forward. Mark and Jack share three gaming technology breakthroughs that will lead to benefits across the gaming industry in the future: 

â€¢ Neural Arrays - this enables a group of compute units to share and process data more efficiently, similar to a single focused AI engine, which unlocks a new level of performance for the next generation of upscaling and denoising technologies. 

â€¢ Radiance Cores - a new dedicated hardware block designed for unified light transport that handles ray tracing and path tracing in real time, which frees up the CPU for geometry and simulation while the GPU focuses on shading and lighting.

â€¢ Universal Compression - a system that evaluates every piece of data added to memory and compresses it whenever possible, which dramatically reduces memory bandwidth usage so the GPU can deliver more detail and higher frame rates with greater efficiency.
